commit_message:
Delete cloned git repos from worker node

While building LP's and DU's, we clone users git repos
locally and build docker images.

Once we are done, we need to delete these repos to avoid
running out of space on the worker nodes.

Check config option before deleting cache

Change-Id: I6e58eb328eb8d8d31e342a7191ccea52cdcd49ef
Closes-bug: 1419169

subject: Delete local languagepack image after building the DU
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-02-10 20:40:20.000000000', 'files': ['solum/worker/handlers/shell.py', 'solum/worker/config.py', 'contrib/lp-cedarish/docker/build-app'], 'message': 'Delete local languagepack image after building the DU

When building a DU based on a custom LP, we download the LP image
to the worker node to build the DU image on top of it.

Once the DU is built, we need to delete the LP from the worker,
else lingering LP images will cause the worker to run out of storage.

- Added a config option to activate this feature

Closes-bug: 1419067

Change-Id: If3fcebe494ff07c8076e0a23a098b10f8384e449
'}]
commit_message:
Delete local languagepack image after building the DU

When building a DU based on a custom LP, we download the LP image
to the worker node to build the DU image on top of it.

Once the DU is built, we need to delete the LP from the worker,
else lingering LP images will cause the worker to run out of storage.

- Added a config option to activate this feature

Closes-bug: 1419067

Change-Id: If3fcebe494ff07c8076e0a23a098b10f8384e449

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-02-09 16:17:44.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/auth/plugins/mapped.py', 'keystone/contrib/federation/utils.py'], 'message': "Change user identification in mapping engine

As federation will allow for direct user mapping defined in the Keystone
backend we need a way to properlly identify users that are being mapped.
That said user is no longer identified as a user's name but a domain can
be specified in the mapping rules and this will be used for proper user
identification.

Partially-Implements bp federated-direct-user-mapping

Change-Id: I64b4691157297e40ed5c91a3f6a84d00cf610048
"}]
commit_message:
Change user identification in mapping engine

As federation will allow for direct user mapping defined in the Keystone
backend we need a way to properlly identify users that are being mapped.
That said user is no longer identified as a user's name but a domain can
be specified in the mapping rules and this will be used for proper user
identification.

Partially-Implements bp federated-direct-user-mapping

Change-Id: I64b4691157297e40ed5c91a3f6a84d00cf610048

cyrus-sasl-plain is no more automatically installed.

commit_message:
Change telemetry client to return one value and update tests

The get/set alarm state methods returned strings so they were left as returning
two values. Checking of success codes was added to the client as that had not

It turns out that when you're looping over a set of params to move them
into an internal dict, returning inside the loop results in processing

Change-Id: If1bf0c22b758e7238846b08991f4b0d25c841583
"}]
commit_message:
Don't return the auth dict inside the loop

It turns out that when you're looping over a set of params to move them
into an internal dict, returning inside the loop results in processing
exactly one of them. This is not, it turns out, what you wanted.

Change-Id: If1bf0c22b758e7238846b08991f4b0d25c841583

commit_message:
Skip functional tests that fail due to a qpidd bug

There is a bug in qpidd that affects the order of message delivery
over AMQP 1.0 links that share the same connection.  Avoid those
functional test that fail due to this bug.

https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-6307

Change-Id: I6e0cdb38cac566c6c9d19ed991f25f8d0d00d355
Closes-bug: #1420456

commit_message:
Make sure we're deep-copying the auth dict

Having a defaults dict that has an empty dict and then does a bunch of
updates means you have ONE instance of a dict that all of the other
instances have references to.

Change-Id: Id008f7ec98ff7b392553cebca5a5b301330e67a3

commit_message:
Install python-openvswitch with openvswitch

A native OVSDB implementation of Neutron's ovs_lib is being added.
It requires the python-openvswitch package which is not yet
available in PyPI. python-openvswitch has no additional dependencies
other than the python interpreter.

Partially-Implements: blueprint vsctl-to-ovsdb
Change-Id: I10ad6a6c05d56987ac1977cc61517edb8f3d237b

commit_message:
Move LB reload logic into scaling library

The lb_reload() logic is moved into a separate module of the scaling
library.  A new test case is added to test this utility function.

Since the revised _lb_reload() method checks if LOAD_BALANCER_NAMES is
defined/provided or not, the OpenStack version of AutoScalingGroup
doesn't have to implement an empty _lb_reload() method now.

partial-blueprint: as-lib
partial-blueprint: reorg-asg-code

Change-Id: I7387d0f27c6121be29d9a035be4cca0b9bbdf441

commit_message:
Refactor event-log code

Now event-log code have few bad points:
1) We push an list in context without any extra info
2) Name event_wrapper_without_instance looks strange
3) Code duplications

This patch remove this bad points and make event-log code better.

Partially implements blueprint event-log

Change-Id: I075d256b4251159b71954e2f7e020cfd4d5e6b9b

commit_message:
Make sure we always notify user about an introspect call error

Previously if list_ports failed, there would be no notifications.
Introduced NodeInfo.add_attribute(), so that we can separate
adding node to cache and adding it's attributes.

Change-Id: Ia654d1a047e94d91522c606bc00941951d9afb10
Closes-Bug: #1413552

commit_message:
Adding /api/ping handler

It's required for proper monitoring of nailgun
I can't use /api/version or /api/releases because I couldn't
rely on HTTP 200 Ok reply only.
I need a handler which won't be changed within development process
or between builds.

Change-Id: Ib1a11159393b6ca8cb9492cf92e61936ffa6a1ed

When we are using devstack plugin approach and ERROR_ON_CLONING
set to true, upstream jobs are failing with below error:
   "Cloning not allowed in this configuration"

This patch resolves this issue by changing ERROR_ON_CLONING to
false while cloning plugin repository.

Change-Id: I36942d133acfb9714119ff403dec513a2e9d2505
'}]
commit_message:
Allow cloning of devstack external plugins

When we are using devstack plugin approach and ERROR_ON_CLONING
set to true, upstream jobs are failing with below error:
   "Cloning not allowed in this configuration"

This patch resolves this issue by changing ERROR_ON_CLONING to
false while cloning plugin repository.

Change-Id: I36942d133acfb9714119ff403dec513a2e9d2505

commit_message:
Cap novaclient

In preparation for releasing a new novaclient cap python-novaclient on
stable/juno to prevent the new release from possibly breaking stable.

Note: There is a in progress patch to pin all stable/juno requirements,
but it isn't ready yet. So do this in the meantime.

Log warning if CONF.my_ip is not found on system

interfaces then log a warning to alert the operators.

commit_message:
Ceilometer ceph storage meters need requests-aws

Ceilometer is using requests-aws to drive functional tests for ceph storage
meters using the ceph radosgw admin ops APIs. Ceph radosgw admin APIs need
the AWS S3 authentication for getting meters information. The request-aws
package used to authenticate the rados admin ops APIs to provide the meter
information to ceilometer during the polling.

corresponding spec: blueprint ceph-ceilometer-integration

Change-Id: I0d6922a86c3104dec542f242474bfa8ea327820b

commit_message:
virt: Fix interaction between disk API tests

A couple of tests were leaking `setUp` state causing the
`test_can_resize_need_fs_type_specified` test to randomly fail.

This probably passed in the gate due to the ordering happening to be correct
everytime. Since I'm using `nosetests`, I happen to be running the tests in
the 'wrong' order.

The solution is to have the tests clean up their state between runs.

Change-Id: Ib9fe973d7784f763ad4714bd39085bc1d256d9c7
Closes-Bug: 1409173

commit_message:
Keystoneclient tests from venv-installed client

The keystoneclient tests were using the library installed from a
git clone. Rather than do a clone of master, the tests will now just
use the keystoneclient installed to the venv.

Doing a `git clone` causes problems on any system without reliable
Internet access, and since the keystoneclient tests have changed to
being for functional tests rather than for verifying
backwards-compatibility of the client, this will make things easier.

(cherry picked from commit 0c407c5f8d1f3654585add3334e535ec0c1b7c28)

Conflicts:

        keystone/tests/test_keystoneclient.py
        keystone/tests/test_keystoneclient_sql.py
        test-requirements-py3.txt
        test-requirements.txt

Change-Id: I079fa77501b8987a4724d03a792b084a6d853e21

commit_message:
Decrease rpc timeout after agent receives SIGTERM

The patch sets different timeout to rpc api objects in OVS agent after
SIGTERM is received. Given timeout is configurable. This action prevents
long waiting for rpc call() methods to timeout and decreases amount of time
needed to successfully stopping OVS agent.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: 1408334

Change-Id: I3026775e813a74bad9e0bca3be1f535212a2e417
(cherry picked from commit d3af7b0d2ebb2dd4da7e4a620eca8f554c124ec6)

commit_message:
Remove use of keepalived 'vrrp_sync_group' as it is unused

Now keepalived configuration wraps the VRRP instances with a
'vrrp_sync_group'. The VRRP sync group functionality is only
relevant when more then one VR instance is contained in it.
In that case the VRs in the group will have the same state.
Our use of keepalived uses a single instance per router.

This patch simply removes the 'vrrp_sync_group'.
In this patch VR instances are used on their own and they now
hold the 'notify_scripts'.

Note that the same VRRP functionality is preserved with this
patch.

Another motiviation for this patch, aside from removing
useless configuration, is to lay the foundation for a future
patch that will the related bug by adding 'track_script'
that are not supported with 'vrrp_sync_group'.

Change-Id: I33b81049cd9cf140244bbf121d1a71492161c77c
Related-Bug: #1365461

commit_message:
Add create-update-delete stack scenario

The create-update-delete stack scenario executes the following
actions with using Heat:
 - creates the new stack (with some resources)
 - updates the stack and stack resoruces with the new template
 - deletes the stack.
Unit-tests for the changes above are also included into patch.

Patch also adds rally test cases for stack create-update-delete
stack scenario (because rally tests require test scenario to be
used by test case samples):
Case 1:
- Heat creates a new stack
- Heat updates the stack with adding additional resource to
the stack
- Heat deletes the stack
Case 2:
- Heat creates a stack
- Heat updates the stack with deleting some resource from the
stack
- Heat deletes the stack.

Change-Id: I4c0ff24d0651434450a281a62670f1bd6c2a0000

commit_message:
L2 gateway agent implementation

The patch provides the following:
1. A base L2 gateway agent and manager that:
   a. periodically sends heart beats to the Neutron server
   b. processes basic RPC (setting the agent type) received from the plugin

2. A variant of L2 gateway agent manager that:
   a. manages connections to the configured OVSDB servers
   b. processes RPCs originated from the plugin destined to the OVSDB servers
   c. notifies to the plugin of any changes in the configured OVSDB servers'
      tables

Partially implements: blueprint l2-gateway-api

Co-Authored-By: vikas<vikas.d-m@hp.com>

Change-Id: I19798e2283a6814dcc9e0f72afe8e1327c78de6b

commit_message:
Add 'verify' option to package.create

PackageManager.create bypasses the base class functions
for making HTTP requests, and as such creating a package
in an environment where an SSL CA cert is configured does not
pass that CA cert to the requests library. This patch fixes this
specific issue, but longer term
https://bugs.launchpad.net/python-muranoclient/+bug/1354129 should
resolve this.

Change-Id: Id61e513089d713bd47d70725a4307f04f4a06ade
Closes-bug: 1419870

commit_message:
Fixes Hyper-V should log a clear error message

When failing to access a remote SMB UNC path, Python raises
   WindowsError: [Error 123] The filename, directory name, or volume
label syntax is incorrect: '\\\\'
This issue happens during resize/cold migration.

This fix ensures that the Nova driver will report a clear error
message.

Change-Id: I735987f3c3f8c16759f6fbbb235a0156df832855
Closes-Bug: #1367786
(cherry pick from commit 42560abdf172bae2df5d3297003324f8c46b8037)

commit_message:
Fix copy-from when user_storage_quota is enabled

If we enable 'user_storage_quota' and try to upload image
then it throws 'AttributeError' error.

If 'user_storage_quota' parameter is enabled then we need to send
image_data as LimitingReader class object to 'store_add_to_backend'
method. But currently we are getting image_data as
CooperativeReader class object every time.

Change-Id: I301d4007c9a4bea8836ee98a9e9685de2104a28e
Closes-Bug: 1398903
(cherry picked from commit 2690d6f18333c4b4eee21b296e7ffbde614ee89f)

commit_message:
Adds service to indicate a user-readable and understandable name

- For documentation purposes, we use a short and consistent word or
phrase for each collection to describe the services it offers.
- I purposely made the capitalization consistent so that these are
now sentence case.

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-02-02 10:09:20.000000000', 'files': ['deployment/puppet/docker/templates/dockerctl_config.erb'], 'message': 'Mount /tmp into Nailgun and MCollective containers

Both Nailgun and MCollective MUST have some common storage directory.
Why? Because Nailgun has to save somewhere uploaded Ubuntu ISO and

Change-Id: I268a768f34bb9bdbc6534765e83ed5df0a254dc0
Implements: blueprint downloadable-ubuntu-release
'}]
commit_message:
Mount /tmp into Nailgun and MCollective containers

Both Nailgun and MCollective MUST have some common storage directory.
Why? Because Nailgun has to save somewhere uploaded Ubuntu ISO and
MCollective has to be able to perform a job against it.

Change-Id: I268a768f34bb9bdbc6534765e83ed5df0a254dc0
Implements: blueprint downloadable-ubuntu-release

commit_message:
Increase body max size in Nginx for upload request

Since we're going to upload Ubuntu ISO we need to increase max size of
client's body request. Otherwise - requests will be rejected by Nginx.

Change-Id: I42dd61f66bfac31b531307a77e987c54648da1ea
Implements: blueprint downloadable-ubuntu-release

commit_message:
Add extract_repos.py to MCollective container

We need to add a script for extracting Ubuntu repos from the ISO to
MCollective container, because we're going to use declarative tasks.
Therefore, Nailgun's concern is just to send task that executes the
script (extract_repos.py) with right arguments.

Change-Id: I780965d712bc5b5c770be756f1edd95eedcdccfd
Implements: blueprint downloadable-ubuntu-release

commit_message:
Implement handler for uploading ISO

Summary:

* Add optional column "release_id" to "tasks" table. We need this
  because since now tasks may be bound to releases, not to clusters.
* Add "processing" state to releases. We need it in order to forbid
  concurrent upload requests.
* Add "prepare_release" task which sends to Astute and RPC call to
  execute two action: extract_repos and build_images.
* Add "execute_tasks_resp" to receiver that's going to update task
  progress.
* Add "prepare_release_resp" to receiver that's updating release
  if task was completed.

Implements: blueprint downloadable-ubuntu-release
Change-Id: Id4eb5fbf9048abd04b6432c9c9de02909c73c890

subject: Ceilometer API fails: bad rabbit_use_ssl setting
revisions:

This patch updates the ceilometer.conf file to avoid an issue
where rabbit_use_ssl got set to <blank> if no Heat metadata
for this setting is provided. Some of our heat templates
(the undercloud for example) do not currently provide this
information and as such Ceilometer API fails to startup
correctly in those deployments.

Change-Id: I0a7dcfb54a0f113e0a3e59e3ccedfe0f485bf12d
Closes-bug: #1416499'}]
commit_message:
Ceilometer API fails: bad rabbit_use_ssl setting

This patch updates the ceilometer.conf file to avoid an issue
where rabbit_use_ssl got set to <blank> if no Heat metadata
for this setting is provided. Some of our heat templates
(the undercloud for example) do not currently provide this
information and as such Ceilometer API fails to startup
correctly in those deployments.

Change-Id: I0a7dcfb54a0f113e0a3e59e3ccedfe0f485bf12d
Closes-bug: #1416499

subject: Use werkzeug to run the developement API server
revisions:
[{'number': 10, 'created': '2015-02-10 18:04:50.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/install.rst', 'gnocchi/rest/app.py', 'requirements.txt'], 'message': 'Use werkzeug to run the developement API server

wsgi.simple_server in a mono threaded process that can handle only
5 requests at a time.

If we use the Gnocchi Ceilometer dispatcher, this one can create
a ton of HTTP connections and most of them received  "connection denied"
errors.

Even the doc recommands to setup Gnocchi through an other WSGI services
like Apache 'mod_wsgi', we can provide a better testing API server.

So this patch changes the default HTTP server to the werkzeug one with
a autodiscovery of number of workers that we can use.

The client queue of werkzeug is 128, so on a 4 cpus machine, gnocchi-api
can now handle 512 connections instead of 5.

Also the change adds references of how to deploy pecan application in
the documentation.

Change-Id: Idbcd8ea3e4d5b67593f9b5a9d69be4316ed39ded
'}]
commit_message:
Use werkzeug to run the developement API server

wsgi.simple_server in a mono threaded process that can handle only
5 requests at a time.

If we use the Gnocchi Ceilometer dispatcher, this one can create
a ton of HTTP connections and most of them received  "connection denied"
errors.

Even the doc recommands to setup Gnocchi through an other WSGI services
like Apache 'mod_wsgi', we can provide a better testing API server.

So this patch changes the default HTTP server to the werkzeug one with
a autodiscovery of number of workers that we can use.

The client queue of werkzeug is 128, so on a 4 cpus machine, gnocchi-api
can now handle 512 connections instead of 5.

Also the change adds references of how to deploy pecan application in
the documentation.

Change-Id: Idbcd8ea3e4d5b67593f9b5a9d69be4316ed39ded

commit_message:
Switching to the default driver for Keystone policies

For now the driver keystone.policy.backends.rules.Policy is used
for Keystone policies. However such basic operations as create/list/
get/update/delete policy are not implemented in this driver. So we
need to use the default driver to be able to create/list/get/update/
delete Keystone policies.

Closes-Bug: #1418973

Change-Id: Ic0758fd5af87d968d2c7ff5a5fab8abc2a44246b

commit_message:
Use unix pattern when syncing deployment tasks

Unix pattern matching will be used when command:

  fuel rel --sync-deployment-tasks

will be executed

By default *tasks.yaml pattern will be used

It can be overwritten by --fp '*another*'.

So in result command should be:

  fuel rel --sync-deployment-tasks --fp '*another*'

implements blueprint granular-deployment-based-on-tasks

commit_message:
Fixing issue with editing N1K network profiles

This resolves issues surrounding the update network profiles
for the Cisco N1K profiles when used with the N1K neutron
plugin.

Issue resolved include the edit form opening up properly
and also addressing which fields are editable and which not.

Also adding new unit tests.
---------

(cherry picked from commit c946139e4e2e81bfdb8f301a35fd1893893bbcb3)

Conflicts:

	openstack_dashboard/dashboards/router/nexus1000v/forms.py
	openstack_dashboard/dashboards/router/nexus1000v/templates/nexus1000v/_update_network_profile.html

Closes-bug: #1260435

The use of this mixin is an overkill, and makes it difficult to modify behavior,
if required.

This patch proposes the same functionality by using composition. Affected tests
are also simplified; as far as I can tell, there is no reason to mock the rpc
notifier the way it was, and this in turn led to the introduction of a setter

Change-Id: I2e59042b4215de2bc39c40bbdb460be8cc766bf1
'}]
commit_message:
Good riddance to L3RpcNotifierMixin

The use of this mixin is an overkill, and makes it difficult to modify behavior,
if required.

This patch proposes the same functionality by using composition. Affected tests
are also simplified; as far as I can tell, there is no reason to mock the rpc
notifier the way it was, and this in turn led to the introduction of a setter
for a property that has no need to be mutable.

Change-Id: I2e59042b4215de2bc39c40bbdb460be8cc766bf1

commit_message:
Map optional arguments as well as required arguments

Optional arguments that are not explicitly required are being ignored
when arguments are being mapped based on inference from atoms' execute
method signatures.  This patch adds support for mapping optional
arguments in addition to required arguments.

Change-Id: I440c02dcd901a563df512e33754b13e3c05d4155

commit_message:
switch to oslo_serialization

oslo.serialization 1.2.0 has moved its namespace from old
oslo.serialization to oslo_serialization, the old import style can
still work, but will not be supported in next release cycle.

Let's sync it.

commit_message:
tox: fix the test suite

fix pep8 syntax (H904 Wrap long lines in parentheses instead of a backslash).

fix two regressions in test_os_svc_daemon.py introduced by
    Ibd491881d79160ad1457526d51512f5fc1cf9ea5:
  - ensure os-svc-daemon won't try to write in /etc/os-logging by passing
    the “-l” extra parameter.
  - fix the test_standard_upstart test from test_os_svc_daemon.py to
     match the expected outpout.

Change-Id: I113504947d126e9d91409f97f8291d5b8fc15c42

commit_message:
Add blueprint ceilometer-gnocchi-alarm

Gnocchi provides two new kind of Ceilometer alarm rules that allows to query
Gnocchi API instead of Ceilometer API to retreive statistics about Ceilometer
monitored metrics.

This blueprint proposes to add the corresponding heat resources:

 * OS::Ceilometer::GnocchiResourcesAlarm
 * OS::Ceilometer::GnocchiMetricsAlarm

Change-Id: I687dcadb56bcf8e3b1ac81745b23fe79688bd83a

revisions:

Reasons:
 - Cassandra service fails to start due to changed permissions
   of cassandra.yaml, this was caused because new file was
   created by another user, so it is required to revert
   ownership to conf file to prevent bootstrap failure.

Changes:
 - adding exec that reverts ownership
   right after config movement.
 - adding exec that sets required permissions

Change-Id: I6baf86c0070067fae2003f074e3f536a7fad8f5f
Closes-Bug: #1415862
'}]
commit_message:
Update cassandra.yaml ownership after write_config operation

Reasons:
 - Cassandra service fails to start due to changed permissions
   of cassandra.yaml, this was caused because new file was
   created by another user, so it is required to revert
   ownership to conf file to prevent bootstrap failure.

Changes:
 - adding exec that reverts ownership
   right after config movement.
 - adding exec that sets required permissions

Change-Id: I6baf86c0070067fae2003f074e3f536a7fad8f5f
Closes-Bug: #1415862

commit_message:
Implement PrivateIpAddress property for EC2::Instance

Implement PrivateIpAddress property for EC2::Instance. When
PrivateIpAddress is provided and SubnetId is not, will raise
StackValidationFailed error. When SubnetId and NetworkInterfaces
are both provided, will raise ResourcePropertyConflict error.

Change-Id: Ia9122862de709a0fbdda53a9fa7ea6a6a4606b27
Closes-Bug: #1327511

commit_message:
Catch exception during resolving outputs

Previously we got error when try to show incorrect outputs.
Now we catch all exceptions and return None value in this case.

Change-Id: I7a7c53c1ad8f42082c89c92cbcb52599a6c7f1f8
Closes-Bug: #1273490
(cherry picked from commit 52adf73d4d8eeb614e6cfffaad2c98b69dccd94d)

commit_message:
Stop installing tempest

We run tempest inside of tox so no nee to install it. By not installing
it we decouple one more thing from the requirements sync.

Without this patch, due to branchless tempest, tempest must work with
master and all stable branch global requirements.

Although installing tempest should work on master, don't install it
anyway to make the user experience more uniform across master and
stable branches.

Note: Long term we can install this inside of a virtualenv
(I92648fffc1ad6af53006a0970722fd15f4e79dc2) but that logic hasn't landed
yet and installing tempest is breaking us. So leave moving this to a
virtualenv for a later patch.

Conflicts:
	lib/tempest

Change-Id: I78d51f04ed01da4ce8aa0e127be028f969d3b4f8
(cherry picked from commit 1368b98669ae9365193f8cd22bdce1c9abdc5499)

commit_message:
Fix backup state check while restoring an instance

Reasons:
 - Trove API service checks backup only for NEW/BUILDING state,
   FAILED state also significant since users are not able to
   restore an instance from FAILED backup.

Changes:
 - adding 'is_done_successfuly' property to DBBackup object;
 - adding status validation at restoring;
 - fake int-tests proposed.

Behaviour:
 - server side raises HTTP Conflict(409) when attempting
   to restore an instance from backup that is still running or failed.

Change-Id: Ide9d0e6f67adaea0c6d99679eba73cebb01c807f
Closes-Bug: #1338996

commit_message:
Update logical-name spec for uuid/name clash

During implementation (review 141737) it was found that it's
not possible to differentiate a logical-name from a UUID via
pattern match, so this patch updates the spec to reflect that
such checking cannot take place.

Change-Id: Iac0d1f6c1f240692126dae1867828d13b99a6341

commit_message:
"neutron help port-update" help info updated

Initially we were unable to see complete help
info for "neutron port-update" command.
Now, with this patch complete help info is
displayed to the user. Apart from the existing
information, the following information will
also be displayed:-
    --name
    --admin-state-up
    --device-id
    --device-owner

Also added the missing --device-owner option in
the help information of "neutron port-create"
command. Added a unit test for above options.

Change-Id: I7a2ea4858568fb9a6d21497b49cb4cfdddc75139
Closes-Bug: #1377360

commit_message:
Use python abc for abstract classes

Instead of raising NotImplementedErrors in abstract methods, mark them as
abstract using python abc class [1].
See also [2]

[1]: http://legacy.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3119/
[2]: http://dbader.org/blog/abstract-base-classes-in-python

Change-Id: Ief9eefc2ae87526248b91abd04b6e62ad94fbf35
Partial-Bug: #1346797

commit_message:
Turn off missing-directory log output for default case

This message is being hit constantly and requiring work-arounds
(e.g. I335a661d307a330e8b59883ef60c787c6590eb42)

It was turned down from a warning in
I183597f23b3a5eb44debd73f7a4a4444ca0d22fd.  As it says there, the
directory missing is considered a normal condition.

I think if someone explicitly sets a directory and it is missing it
should warn, but skip the output completely for the default.

Change-Id: Ib749b2a019c89bec811d3da5a369ffcdd27bc76f

subject: API: Improve status api code and add tests
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2015-02-10 21:39:30.000000000', 'files': ['contrib/tempest/tempest/scenario/test_congress_basic_ops.py', 'congress/tests/test_congress.py', 'congress/api/status_model.py', 'congress/server/congress_server.py', 'congress/tests/api/test_status_model.py'], 'message': "API: Improve status api code and add tests

The status API was setup as a CollectionHandler though the API request
was structured to be handled by an ElementHandler this get_items() was
being called instead of get_item(). In addition, nothing was setup to
ever call get_item. This patch corrects the structure and configures it
to be an ElementHandler.

In additon, this patch changes the status api so that responses are now
returned in this format: {'last_updated': 'now', 'last_error': 'foo'}
previously: {'results': [{'last_updated': 'now'}, {'last_error': 'foo'}]}

Lastly, this patch adds code coverage for this api.

Change-Id: Icb245cf9f21d8cef3cc45a47df98038c760c9770
"}]
commit_message:
API: Improve status api code and add tests

The status API was setup as a CollectionHandler though the API request
was structured to be handled by an ElementHandler this get_items() was
being called instead of get_item(). In addition, nothing was setup to
ever call get_item. This patch corrects the structure and configures it
to be an ElementHandler.

In additon, this patch changes the status api so that responses are now
returned in this format: {'last_updated': 'now', 'last_error': 'foo'}
previously: {'results': [{'last_updated': 'now'}, {'last_error': 'foo'}]}

Lastly, this patch adds code coverage for this api.

Change-Id: Icb245cf9f21d8cef3cc45a47df98038c760c9770

commit_message:
Adds policy enforcement unittest base class for v2.1

This base class is used to test policy enforcement for v2.1.
We can use this class to call controller method.

This patch also add overwrite parameter for set_rules of PolicyFixture,
that can clear all the rules, then only set the rule what we expected.

Partially implements bp v3-api-policy

Change-Id: I001c5c4a8381630b4424a4be8dd63eeed43bdd7d

commit_message:
Fixing issue with detection of the Keystone openstack process.

The monasca-setup process was matching on "keystone" in the command line
which contains "--keystone_url" in the command-line.  This was causing a
false positive on boxes that don't have keystone installed.

Change-Id: I264ce508e49fc0486ef7fc22bdccd073292c57aa

commit_message:
Config parameters beginning with "oozie." should be in job properties file

In the Oozie EDP engine, look for configs beginning with 'oozie.' and
pass them to _get_oozie_job_params() as additional values to be written
to the job properties file. Do not allow the workflow application path
to be overwritten (oozie.wf.application.path) since it is generated by
EDP. Prevent configs beginning with 'oozie.' from being written to the
workflow.xml file in workflow_factory.py

Closes-Bug: 1419923
Change-Id: I75b60e5bc3d1afadac7c2b209e3ea68e4ba9e88b

commit_message:
Fix detach volume from host problem in VMAX driver

The VMAX driver unmaps a volume from a host without checking
the host info in the connector, resulting the wrong host to be
detached. This patch looks up the host info before detach and
fixes the problem.

Closes-Bug: #1382641
Change-Id: I68f053b34cc68cdb4f3a9e622faa47a260abd53a

commit_message:
Warn about zookeeper service group driver usage

The zookeeper service group driver is untested by openstack, the unit
tests are skipped since the py27 jobs in infra don't have a zookeeper
backend and there is no experimental queue job that runs tempest against
zookeeper or third party CI, so log a warning about the risk in using
it.

Change-Id: Ic6a53f56a1ad4cb699c06c83228e9e38b6c21fb2

commit_message:
Improve status API

The congress-server previously returned the status api response as:
{'results': [{'last_updated': 'now'}, {'last_error': 'foo'}]} though
it would be better if it returned it as:
{'last_updated': 'now', 'last_error': 'foo'}. This patch fixes the client
side of this api call and also corrects the cli command to say show over list.
There is also a server side patch as well that is required for this.

Change-Id: I869d74fac424e608ceeca1984eef9ae73c38dd42

commit_message:
Make datasources configurable via the API

This patch allows datasources to be configured via the API. It exposes a new
api call /v1/drivers/<driver> which returns the configuration
needed by a driver in order to configure it. Then, a user will make a post to
/v1/data-sources with the config to create the datasource.

This patch  makes a few structural changes to congress the most noted that it
makes d6Cage a singleton which is needed to be able to dynamically add new
datasources to the message bus.

Also, lots of the API code was changed in order to start moving toward an API
that supports multi tenancy which should now be easy to add.

I apologize that this patch set is so big though the scope of changes needed
to be down to support a configurable API were large and through out many
places in the code. Several cleanup patches will be push on top of this which
should be easier to review.

Implements blueprint: api-configurable-datasources

Change-Id: If82b505e1835254216e19eb1c55a035d2c0b8a3e

commit_message:
Keystoneclient tests from venv-installed client

The keystoneclient tests were using the library installed from a
git clone. Rather than do a clone of master, the tests will now just
use the keystoneclient installed to the venv.

Doing a `git clone` causes problems on any system without reliable
Internet access, and since the keystoneclient tests have changed to
being for functional tests rather than for verifying
backwards-compatibility of the client, this will make things easier.

Conflicts:

	.testr.conf
	keystone/tests/core.py
	keystone/tests/test_keystoneclient.py
	keystone/tests/test_keystoneclient_sql.py
	test-requirements-py3.txt
	test-requirements.txt

Change-Id: I079fa77501b8987a4724d03a792b084a6d853e21
(cherry picked from commit 0c407c5f8d1f3654585add3334e535ec0c1b7c28)
(cherry picked from commit 7a613ae4f14d30fbe4452f2cc8bc2a657d41ffd4)

commit_message:
Call controller methods directly in test_multinic

In API unit testing, making call through WSGI is little bit overhead,
wherever applicable, unit tests can make direct call to controller
methods.
Also URL given in controller method's request is not used
(for direct call to controller methods), so pass blank URL
to avoid confusion as tests are shared between V2 & V2.1

This patch makes above cleanup in test_multinic.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I338e342c0fced8683e36ce0a4fca3b5393eb0b4e

commit_message:
Cells: Improve invalid hostname handling

The invalid hostnames that Tempest generates for the negative testing
don't include cells routing paths.  This generates an AttributeError in
the cells service which is not handled by the API.  This is changed to
be a proper NovaException which is caught and handled by the API.

saved, and the driver will try to get the information again in
every subsequent call. For a driver running on a system with no

commit_message:
Cache empty results in libvirt get_volume_connector

The libvirt driver's get_volume_connector is called on each
connection. The iSCSI initiator name and FC HBA information is
obtained and saved in instance variables on the first call, and
these values are used in subsequent calls. However, if no
information is returned from any of these calls, this is not
saved, and the driver will try to get the information again in
every subsequent call. For a driver running on a system with no
iSCSI initiator configured, this means trying and failing to
read a file each time. For a system with no FC HBA, this
results in two calls to systool for each connect.

This patch distinguishes between the case of the first call
and subsequent calls where the connection information was not
found. This speeds up connection times for systems that don't
have both iSCSI and FC configured. Note a behavioral change
that if iSCSI is not configured, or if the FC HBA is not present,
at the first connection, the service will have to be restarted
for the connection information to be used. I believe this is
a very uncommon scenario.

Closes-Bug: #1406484
Change-Id: I233e4559baa0818353897e04c84501858a59febb

commit_message:
Disable install tempest by default

In I78d51f04ed01da4ce8aa0e127be028f969d3b4f8 we turned off installing
tempest because we install it on stable branches where the stable reqs
do not equal the tempest master (branchless) reqs.

And in Ie4ea7335a57917244873ec54658ca269ab765ce1 we enable install
tempest by default. But we want to disable this in all gating
environments, because we need this off in stable branches and we should
try to make master and stable branches as similar as possible.

Note: this doesn't mean anything in stable branches yet, but it will
once we cut a devstack branch for Kilo, (At which point we probably
should change the default devstack value to False on stable)

Change-Id: I47695335e3f254711bb906af247667392435ff0c

commit_message:
Make gate-ceilometer-python34 only run on master branch

d64ff557f774b2b16a755675c9c4f34ddd7c1dd3 originally made the py33 job
only run on master but that was before stable/juno existed. The py34 job
is failing on stable/juno because a
ceilometer dependency (happybase) doesn't support py3 yet and the
ceilometer tox.ini doesn't have a py34 target on stable/juno, that was
added to master with commit 8883fa9801579c28c4b36fca611008fc81ca1045.

We could backport the tox.ini change to stable/juno but there doesn't
seem to be much point in running a handful of py3 tests for ceilometer
on stable so make the job only run on master.

There is also some related history for stable/icehouse in change
Ie58fdd755137c4ed8ff53b1f16819bd3a8ebcdf8.

Change-Id: Ifef79456e7caea8ecc5dda6b0ea8b6869eb99f93
Closes-Bug: #1420433

commit_message:
Add a eventlet utils helper module

When greenthreads are being used (and/or eventlet is available and
some modules have been monkey-patched) emit warnings to the users
that certain modules should be monkey-patched and if they are not
then spurious or unexpected lock-ups and/or hangs may result due to
this type of mixed usage which doesn't typically end well.

This commit adds that functionality to a new eventlet utils module
that can be used by calling code when that code really knows it will
not work without modules being patched or partially being patched.

Change-Id: I9a856fc0a6502b438c8da9b2f589154a6fa89a9f

commit_message:
move add event creation logic to keystonemiddleware

currently, the logic to create audit events is contained in pyCADF.
this makes it extremely difficult to modify as changes often require
edits to two different libraries, and subsequent releases of two
different libraries. additionally, it makes it impossible to test the
full path. this patch attempts to minimise the chaos.

Change-Id: Ic0ca193139acaa751cd96e7fadad2223a84088c8

commit_message:
Refactor processing of testr artifacts for reuse

Previously, only testr artifacts for tempest were being processed on
cleanup.  Functional jobs for neutron and neutron-vnpaas have adding
their own artifact processing into hook scripts to work around this
limitation, but this duplication of effort is costly.

This change refactors the existing artifact processing so it can be
configurably targeted at any project's testr artifacts.  The
DEVSTACK_GATE_TESTR_ARTIFACT_TARGET environment variable can be set to
the repo path name (e.g. 'neutron') to ensure that artifacts are
correctly processed for that project.

commit_message:
Output logs of policy index

To make it easier for Swift operators to specify problematic devices,
a policy index will be recorded in log files of proxy and storage servers
for each user request which is related to storage policy.

This patch simply adds 'storage_policy_index' field in a log format.
If there is no specified policy index, '-' is output in this field.

Extra fix: Doc about the log line of storage nodes now properly reflects
           'server_pid' field.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I7286ae85bcbcec73b5377dc115cbdb0f57d1b025
Implements: blueprint logging-policy-number

commit_message:
Revert "Turn off sitepackages"

On a fresh system, I am seeing an issue where a DevStack run exits with
an error when trying to set up and configure Tempest. Tox attempts to
install dependencies into /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/
without invoking sudo privileges.

This reverts commit 9f1612e7afd9de56bc70d5c5b1c63ad5181d84ab.

Change-Id: Ic72f84d7d8600f20465a972aeaeec19ccf93df21
Closes-Bug: #1420480

commit_message:
Adjust Cinder to support FCP on System z systems

There are some platform specific changes needed to allow Cinder to
support FCP on System z: the System z specific format of the device file
paths, adding and removing devices explicitely, and ignoring vHBAs which
are offline.
Partial-Implements blueprint linux-systemz

Change-Id: Ia61c37246235bec618de5bb7f718e8b5520bc9ae

commit_message:
Modify datasource api and add datasource-driver api bindings

This patch adds bindings to read the datasource-drivers config/schema
from congress server. It also changes several methods so the look ups
are now done by id instead of name. We needed to change this in the server
api so we can have a multi tenant api.

commit_message:
Fix kafka_consumer detection plugin for localhost

If no host.name is specified in /etc/kafka/server.properties, the
kafka_consumer detection plugin is supposed to use 'localhost' for
its kafka connect string, but this is not working, causing this
output when running monasca-setup:

INFO:   Kafka found listening on :9092
ERROR: Unable to connect to kafka broker at :9092

I also altered the output a bit because defaulting to localhost is
not really an error.

Change-Id: I6cf03a39c1f40cd12a31e31922af73b3216ee582

commit_message:
Added install script for zookeeper

This script installs zookeeper.  The script expects a unique ID for the
node being provisioned and a list of IPs for all zookeeper nodes.

The script has been tested on Ubuntu 14.04 (trusty) and Debian 7
(wheezy).  The included Vagrantfile can be used to bring up a 3 node
test cluster.

[{'number': 6, 'created': '2015-02-10 18:28:06.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/virt/xenapi/test_xenapi.py'], 'message': "network: Fix IPv6 tests for Mac

Some network tests would fail on a Mac because the IPv6 addressed returned
wasn't an exact match due to a difference in the `socket.inet_ntop` function
that `netaddr` uses.

On a Mac 0 parts of the IPv6 are compressed away to '::' whereas on Linux they
remain ':0:'.

Ultimately, the fix should be in the upstream `netaddr` library which already
has an issue logged for it: https://github.com/drkjam/netaddr/issues/82

commit_message:
network: Fix IPv6 tests for Mac

Some network tests would fail on a Mac because the IPv6 addressed returned
wasn't an exact match due to a difference in the `socket.inet_ntop` function
that `netaddr` uses.

On a Mac 0 parts of the IPv6 are compressed away to '::' whereas on Linux they
remain ':0:'.

Ultimately, the fix should be in the upstream `netaddr` library which already
has an issue logged for it: https://github.com/drkjam/netaddr/issues/82

Until that's fixed, the solution is to skip the offending tests.

Co-Authored-By: Johannes Erdfelt <johannes@erdfelt.com>
Change-Id: I7a8a49f4105079a686e553b4d002f04a26b93d0f
Closes-Bug: 1409135

commit_message:
Check service status before add host to aggregate

When a compute service is disabled, tried to add it to an aggregate
that is exported as an availabilty zone will result in
IndexError: pop from empty list exception in API log
This patch fixs the problem by checking whether the service is disabled
then raise error to user instead of 500 internal error.

There can be another alternative, to involve disabled service into
availability zone, but it will make an availability zone has
enabled and disabled services and make the logic complicated,
 So only use partial bug to indicate this
patch fixs part of the bug, further fix might need a bp.

Change-Id: If66c8c9a364256f57b109ef194ecb5164aa80b18
Partial-Bug: #1419115

commit_message:
Deletes duplicated information on plug-ins from main docs

Currently, information on plug-ins is duplicated
in several sources: Plugin Catalog, User Guide and Fuel Plug-in
Guide.

To provide a single entry point, I suggest removing
instructions on specific plug-ins from User and Plug-in Guide with
leaving common information only.

Change-Id: I9f950e9afc180377d050545033bbaf9aef4aef80

commit_message:
Fix missing ca-certificate parameter to get_auth.

Missing cacert parameter in get_auth_1_0() and it makes requests_args['verify']
is True in default(likes "swift --os-cacert ssl.crti list").
The requests_args['verify'] should be a ca-certificate file name("ssl.crt").

Change-Id: Id3110f3818f55922ad19eeb1ead80fface824009
Closes-Bug: 1418473

commit_message:
Run javelin2 inside of tempest venv

In I78d51f04ed01da4ce8aa0e127be028f969d3b4f8 we are moving away from
installing tempest, instead we should run it in its own tox based virtual
environment so we don't need to make master tempest compatible with
stable/icehouse global requirements.

When a HA router is being deleted with 'python-neutronclient'
while it has an attached interface the deletion will fail since
the router is in use. The order in which the deletion
is done is - first remove the HA interfaces from DB and
then delete the router. In this case the HA interfaces were
indeed deleted but the router itself was not (router is in use).
This causes the DB to be inconsistent where an HA router
exists in the DB while it's ports were removed from the DB.

This patch simply deletes the router first, and then
we know it's safe to remove it's HA interfaces as
well. If the router is in use and deletion fails
the HA interfaces remain intact.

Closes-Bug: #1402698

Change-Id: I956d0094ae6e2412e859d79feeb4003941d2bb4b
"}]
commit_message:
Deleting HA router with attached port causes DB inconsistencies

When a HA router is being deleted with 'python-neutronclient'
while it has an attached interface the deletion will fail since
the router is in use. The order in which the deletion
is done is - first remove the HA interfaces from DB and
then delete the router. In this case the HA interfaces were
indeed deleted but the router itself was not (router is in use).
This causes the DB to be inconsistent where an HA router
exists in the DB while it's ports were removed from the DB.

This patch simply deletes the router first, and then
we know it's safe to remove it's HA interfaces as
well. If the router is in use and deletion fails
the HA interfaces remain intact.

Closes-Bug: #1402698

Change-Id: I956d0094ae6e2412e859d79feeb4003941d2bb4b

commit_message:
Turn our auth plugin into a token interface

This auth plugin is already going to be distributed to everyone so that
they can use it to talk to use the current authentication to talk to
other services. Given that it knows everything that auth_token
middleware knows it may as well be the base for generating policy
contexts.

Implements: bp auth-context-object
Change-Id: I15e3517e854ef110987e392510c6de0f14645a59

subject: modified worker to exit gracefully
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-02-10 19:09:51.000000000', 'files': ['cue/taskflow/service.py', 'cue/cmd/worker.py'], 'message': 'modified worker to exit gracefully

Inserted a workaround for taskflow that was preventing the worker from
exiting gracefully on a ctrl+c.  Also took out oslo.service references

commit_message:
modified worker to exit gracefully

Inserted a workaround for taskflow that was preventing the worker from
exiting gracefully on a ctrl+c.  Also took out oslo.service references
as the inclusion of eventlet was creating problems with kazoo and
taskflow.

commit_message:
Refactor auth_uri handling

The auth_uri setting is the value that's returned on auth failure
in the WWW-Authenticate header. It's not actually used by auth_token
to communicate with the identity server, so the IdentityServer
class doesn't need to know what the setting is for the auth_token
middleware. IdentityServer only needs to know how to provide the
default auth uri (based on how IdentityServer is configured) to the
auth_token middleware in case auth_uri isn't specified.

This change is moving things around to clarify how the auth_uri is
used.

Change-Id: I97aeef5721a044422929c72e9e53898822bcdabf

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 3153, 'name': 'Emilien Macchi', 'email': 'emilien@redhat.com', 'username': 'emilienm'}, {'_account_id': 7155, 'name': 'Sebastien Badia', 'email': 'seb@sebian.fr', 'username': 'sbadia'}, {'_account_id': 8482, 'name': 'Colleen Murphy', 'email': 'colleen@gazlene.net', 'username': 'krinkle'}, {'_account_id': 9060, 'name': 'Mike Dorman', 'email': 'dorm@dorm.org', 'username': 'gd-mdorman'}, {'_account_id': 9983, 'name': 'Richard Megginson', 'email': 'rmeggins@redhat.com', 'username': 'rmeggins'}, {'_account_id': 14910, 'name': 'Michael Renner', 'email': 'robe@amd.co.at'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-01-28 09:13:35.000000000', 'files': ['lib/puppet/provider/keystone_user_role/openstack.rb'], 'message': "Implement caching lookup for keystone_user_role

The new implementation of keystone_user_role failed to implement a
previously existing method, user_role_hash, which helped cache the user
role matrix. This helped prevent subsequent runs of exists? from
re-requesting full lists of projects, users, and roles for every found
instance of keystone_user_role. The failure to implement this caching
causes extremely slow puppet runs even when no changes were needed
since the provider would rebuild the hash for every call of exists?,
which even for a small number of users and projects is very time
consuming.

Additionally, the new implementation introduced a bug in the destroy
method where it might cause a failure if the user had some role in a
project, but not all the roles in the roles property of the resource.

It was also realized that since this provider does not make use of the
flush method, the initializer was not needed.

This patch addresses the issues with the following:

- Adds a class method user_role_hash() for caching the matrix as a class
  instance variable so that the value found in self.instances() can be
  used in the next call to exists?()
- Adds a class method self.set_user_role_hash() for setting the class
  instance variable so that instance methods can set it
- Attempts to get the cached value in self.build_user_role_hash() and
  sets it after making the API request if it was empty
- Changes the exists? method look up the cached value from
  self.instances if it is there, and if not, make only one request for
  the user role list for the given project and use those values to
  create the property hash
- Changes the destroy method use the value from the property hash
  instead of the resource to determine what roles to remove
- Changes the roles method to use the value from the property hash
- Remove the object methods 'instances' and 'build_user_role_hash'
  since there is no longer any reason for an instance method to try to
  build the whole hash
- Change the object method 'instance' to use the cached hash instead of
  attempting to rebuild it
- Removes the initialize method since @property_flush does not need to
  be initialized in this provider.

Change-Id: Ifa67ef60e536f88bded0e8db984728f9bd76b75c
"}]
commit_message:
Implement caching lookup for keystone_user_role

The new implementation of keystone_user_role failed to implement a
previously existing method, user_role_hash, which helped cache the user
role matrix. This helped prevent subsequent runs of exists? from
re-requesting full lists of projects, users, and roles for every found
instance of keystone_user_role. The failure to implement this caching
causes extremely slow puppet runs even when no changes were needed
since the provider would rebuild the hash for every call of exists?,
which even for a small number of users and projects is very time
consuming.

Additionally, the new implementation introduced a bug in the destroy
method where it might cause a failure if the user had some role in a
project, but not all the roles in the roles property of the resource.

It was also realized that since this provider does not make use of the
flush method, the initializer was not needed.

This patch addresses the issues with the following:

- Adds a class method user_role_hash() for caching the matrix as a class
  instance variable so that the value found in self.instances() can be
  used in the next call to exists?()
- Adds a class method self.set_user_role_hash() for setting the class
  instance variable so that instance methods can set it
- Attempts to get the cached value in self.build_user_role_hash() and
  sets it after making the API request if it was empty
- Changes the exists? method look up the cached value from
  self.instances if it is there, and if not, make only one request for
  the user role list for the given project and use those values to
  create the property hash
- Changes the destroy method use the value from the property hash
  instead of the resource to determine what roles to remove
- Changes the roles method to use the value from the property hash
- Remove the object methods 'instances' and 'build_user_role_hash'
  since there is no longer any reason for an instance method to try to
  build the whole hash
- Change the object method 'instance' to use the cached hash instead of
  attempting to rebuild it
- Removes the initialize method since @property_flush does not need to
  be initialized in this provider.

Change-Id: Ifa67ef60e536f88bded0e8db984728f9bd76b75c

commit_message:
Do not depend on endpoint id existing in the service catalog

Currently, if the endpoint id does not exist, pycadf will break.
This patch will attempt to find the id of the endpoint and if not
found, set it to unknown.

commit_message:
Warn if multiple replicas are stored within same region/zone/node

This patch shows a warning to the user if there is a tier (region, zone, node)
at risk because it stores too many replicas. For example, with two regions and 3
replicas it is expected to store at least one replica in each region.

This happens when there is a region, zone or node with a total weight of all
devices bigger than (total weight of all devices in the ring) / (number of
replicas).

The warning also includes he number of partitions per replica per tier.

Closes-Bug: 1400497

Change-Id: Ie9d48a5f71e2c33c0131fc60b4cac51ef8357c54

commit_message:
Add PCI Passthrough/SR-IOV support

The main issue with INI files, it doesn't support complex structures
which end up being declared as strings. This approach get that chain of
character and verify it's a valid JSON equivalent before assigning the
value.

Another driver is even though Hiera supports complex structure, we tend
to keep it simple when using Hiera interpolations.

https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/SR-IOV-Passthrough-For-Networking#SR-IOV_Configuration

Change-Id: I27d43af13fcc80f41a16c31a0a6cfe112dc96acb

commit_message:
Separate the codes of CDH5 and CDH5.3.0

We use v5 and v5.3.0 to put different python files for CDH5 and
CDH5.3.0. CDH5 is CDH5.0.0, we use the name "CDH5" instead of
"CDH5.0.0" for backward support. Currently since CDH5.0.0 does
not support cm_api>6, we cannot use first_run API in CDH5.0.0, so
we only implemented parts of the services that we implemented in
CDH5.3.0.

implements bp: cdh-version-management
Change-Id: I3b3058f25912ddf6206d64db88ac40138a45a53f

keepalived processes. This is an issue if the L3 agent crashes

commit_message:
SIGHUP keepalived if L3 agent restarts

Currently restarting the L3 agent does not SIGHUP any running
keepalived processes. This is an issue if the L3 agent crashes
and is then restarted by an external tool. In this case, the L3
agent resyncs with the controller but does not SIGHUP keepalived.

It's also an issue during upgrades.

Closes-Bug: #1412542
Change-Id: Iec29b483f499f02c593f6e0663c7f3504c615c1a

commit_message:
Adds networking-hyperv in StackForge

networking-hyperv is a library containing the Hyper-V Neutron
Agent, Security Groups Driver, ML2 Mechanism Driver and the
utils modules they use in order to properly bind neutron ports
on a Hyper-V host.

networking-hyperv resulted from the neutron core vendor
decomposition.

Supports Python 2.7 and Python 3.3.

Change-Id: I6979b69d202a7257b34d427c444cade2cef69ad9

commit_message:
Add '--dhcp-leasefile' option to dnsmasq

Dnsmasq forgets vm's leases when restart dnsmasq.
Dnsmasq will sends DHCPNAK when the client tries to
renew its leases. The '--dhcp-leasefile' option will
record every vms lease info, so vms network don't have
to lose ip address.

Change-Id: I931e2ba402606e1cce326d4e9aac5288b271e19e

commit_message:
Add support for keypair-add command reading public key from stdin

If given filename is `-` for `--pub-key` option, reads public key
from stdin.

  $ cat id_rsa.pub | nova keypair-add --pub-key - keyname

Closes-Bug: #1333476

commit_message:
Make more blockinfo functions private.

These are not referenced outside of blockinfo (other than for testing):

* update_bdm
* has_default_ephemeral
* get_device_name
* get_config_drive_type
* get_next_disk_info
* is_disk_bus_valid_for_virt
* find_disk_dev_for_disk_bus
* get_dev_count_for_disk_bus

commit_message:
Fix the rgw apache CI tests

This fixes various issues with the rgw apache CI tests:

* the test did not properly check for success as the curl always exits
with 0, even when the HTTP return code is 401 / unauthorized
* there was a missing dependency to wait until the OSD is ready
* changing the tested versions to be in sync with all other tests.
* cleaning up left over files when uninstalling
* autogenerate the pools

Change-Id: I28dacb1a18e20429f93f2f9996f8196a1d992374

commit_message:
Fix dependency tree to include necessary package ceph

The file /var/lib/ceph/radosgw needs package ceph as a dependency,
because the parent directory /var/lib/ceph is not necessarily present
otherwise.

The cleanest way to achieve that is to make sure all packages tagged
ceph are present.

Change-Id: Ic861e1fb3b3c556961ac8f9026a50863dff7f9e1

Restart 'statsenderd' after changing Collector IP

usage stats during system tests we need to restart
'statsenderd' daemon after changing settings.

commit_message:
Adds barbican keymgr wrapper

Adds a barbican keymgr wrapper to the key manager interface in
nova.  This allows barbican to be configured as the key manager
for encryption keys in nova.  The wrapper translates calls from
the existing key manager interface to python-barbicanclient.

Change-Id: I110c7ceada48de28cee1169b643b12407f21b36c
Implements: blueprint encryption-with-barbican
DocImpact

commit_message:
Remove VPN specific exception

This exception is an overkill, and can be safely removed. The tests
affected were not designed to cover any regression as they were asserting
that the mocked Exception was being raised, defeating the very purpose of
catching the regression; they have been revised to ensure that the checks
are not misplaced in future revision of the code, or that they behave the
way they are supposed to.

Partially-Implements: blueprint services-split
Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/153543/

Change-Id: I22cc8cd4383259dd4ee20bcbc041d589172d88c8

commit_message:
The vcenter_vmdk system test expects to fail two OSTF tests

The system test 'vcenter_vmdk' expected to fail an only OSTF test
'Launch instance, create snapshot, launch instance from snapshot'.
But because of wrong CirrOS image an another OSTF fails too:
'Create volume and attach it to instance'. Both of them should be expected
as failed in that test case.

Change-Id: I5ec0bf366409a69d0a1cfd2ef041318a6fee6a10

commit_message:
Support SR-IOV mechanism driver in ML2

* Rename neutron::plugins::ml2::driver to
  neutron::plugins::ml2::type_driver to allow a namespace flexibility.
* Add neutron::plugins::ml2::mech_driver to follow type drivers
  configuration model.
* Add support to configure specific parameters for SR-IOV mechanism
  driver in adding parameters in both neutron::plugins::ml2 and
  neutron::plugins::ml2::mech_driver.
* Add a unit test with a new context when running SR-IOV mechanism
  driver.
* Configure SR-IOV parameters in standard ML2 configuration file to
  avoid packaging issue if neutron-server does not load ml2_conf_sriov.ini.
* Add neutron-sriov-nic-agent support with neutron::agents::ml2::sriov
* Add unit tests for neutron::agents::ml2::sriov

Source:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/SR-IOV-Passthrough-For-Networking

Change-Id: I724e8bdf48619f00af2c198714f2e4a69f968cab

commit_message:
Manila NetApp cDOT driver refactoring

The Manila cDOT driver is a single file exceeding 1200 lines.  It contains
multiple things (driver code, protocol helpers, ZAPI invocation code,
options) that should be split apart to allow for easier maintenance and
readability and add the potential for code sharing when we reintroduce
a 7-mode driver, add a single-SVM cDOT driver, etc.

We recently refactored NetApp's DOT Cinder drivers into a 4-layer
structure (interface, library, client, API) that separates concerns and
achieves the goals set forth above.  This commit satisfies a plan to
do the same thing in Manila.  The implementation steps are:

1. Update directory structure to match that of the Cinder NetApp drivers
2. Create driver interface shim
3. Move driver code to library (with base & C-mode classes, to allow for
   7-mode code sharing later)
4. Move protocol helpers to separate files (already organized by base &
   C-mode classes)
5. Split out ZAPI code to client layer (with base & C-mode classes, to
   allow for 7-mode code sharing later)
6. Implement NetApp driver factory as in Cinder
7. Implement common NetApp options file as in Cinder
8. Implement cDOT API call optimizations
9. Update all unit tests as needed

Note that this patch appears to treble the total number of code lines.
This is due to the addition of many more unit tests plus a large amount
of fake controller API data to feed the API client tests.

Implements: blueprint netapp-manila-cdot-driver-refactoring
Closes-Bug: #1410317
Partial-Bug: #1396953
Closes-Bug: #1370965
Closes-Bug: #1418690
Closes-Bug: #1418696

Change-Id: I3fc0d09adf84a3708f110a89a7c8c760f4ce3588

commit_message:
metering data ttl sql backend breaks resource metadata

The implementation for sql clear_expired_metering_data() uses delete()
on join() for four metatada tables, which will cause clear whole
tables no matter what join returns. And it associates metadata id
with sample id which makes no sense, the metadata id is resource's
internal id.

Change-Id: I98219bf27a0a765838d45386b7ae6b6b980b1ae9
Closes-Bug: #1419239

commit_message:
Zuul: Ignore dependencies in merge-check

When running a Zuul with support for cross-repo-dependencies, the
merge-check pipeline gets needlessly crowded because of all of the
stacked dependencies.  Set the option to ignore dependencies for
that pipeline.  (Essentially this preserves the current behavior.)

This requires the change to Zuul that adds this option to land.

Change-Id: Ic71471cffa94f393bc1bf6865066cc9d6ad5261f
Depends-On: I553446374ac12aa3e3f2e4bbea7ca8fafba42294

commit_message:
Fix SecurityGroupExists error when booting instances

Make sure we properly handle the case when multiple threads check
and create the default security group, if it hasn't existed yet.
One thread will succeed and others will fail (we have a unique
constraint in db to prevent a race condition), so just handle the
exception to let instance boot proceed.

Steps to reproduce:

1) install OpenStack with Rally using DevStack:

    https://github.com/stackforge/rally/tree/master/contrib/devstack

2) fetch the Rally task:

    http://boris-42.github.io/boot.yaml

3) run it

    rally -v task start boot.yaml

Closes-Bug: #1370782

Conflicts:
        nova/tests/db/test_db_api.py

Change-Id: I414637a31b0b540fefa6c1314be6e973e2d4a178

commit_message:
move from macro install-chefdk to chef-bootstrap

* removed macro 'install-chefdk' in favor of 'chef-bootstrap'
* macro 'chef-bootstrap' executes a cookbook specific bootstrap
  scipt which preconfigures the testnode (install packages and
  dependencies) before running the tests from the Rakefile with the job
  template 'gate-{name}-chef-rake'
* currently the bootstrap.sh does not exist in all cookbooks, since this
  is a experimental job and the final bootstrap.sh will be defined after
  this patch is merged and then cloned/added to all cookbooks using this
  job

Change-Id: I4d622b7b594aa185dd1165c913764aaeced9faae
blueprint: bootstrap-infra-test-nodes

and puppet-tripleo.

As part of this change we also drop the normal tripleo check

and is a waste of resources.  Only the puppet tests would

commit_message:
Rework delegated roles

In deployments that have keystone only nodes, the keystone nodes will
need to configure the keystone roles, but they will not have a heat.conf
file. This means that the functionality between writing the config file
and configuring the role is split. The old role configuration is left in
engine as a deprecated parameter.

Fixes-bug: #1409977

Change-Id: I84a53c4992bcdfc4440560b78c602d517a18ec39
(cherry picked from commit a4af24cb2f00a413e35d87e078807659addf5d55)

commit_message:
Stop installing tempest

We run tempest inside of tox so no nee to install it. By not installing
it we decouple one more thing from the requirements sync.

Without this patch, due to branchless tempest, tempest must work with
master and all stable branch global requirements.

Although installing tempest should work on master, don't install it
anyway to make the user experience more uniform across master and
stable branches.

Note: Long term we can install this inside of a virtualenv
(I92648fffc1ad6af53006a0970722fd15f4e79dc2) but that logic hasn't landed
yet and installing tempest is breaking us. So leave moving this to a
virtualenv for a later patch.

Conflicts:
	lib/tempest

Change-Id: I78d51f04ed01da4ce8aa0e127be028f969d3b4f8
(cherry picked from commit 1368b98669ae9365193f8cd22bdce1c9abdc5499)

commit_message:
Add page_title mixin to all templates

There was a lot of code duplicated across the various templates to do
with setting the page heading. Using the PageTitleMixin this patch
reduces the code for this, down to a single line in each
view.

Change-Id: I3382dfad00e1efe4b65394e930ecb3400f40f50e
Closes-Bug: 1413749

commit_message:
Don't run thirdparty tests on icehouse

Because of incompatibilities between the latest boto and the version
supported on stable/icehouse we can't run the tempest tests with the
latest boto against icehouse nova. This is blocking efforts to isolate
tempest in a venv for gate runs which is needed to unwedge other
issues.

Related-Bug: #1419913
Change-Id: I28e4a14a0b8617af5735e70245416bd35171092c

commit_message:
Remove stable-compat jobs from pycadf

Similar to 20152cf5b32cea94a3860750036efc80bc6b3b46,

This library is already capped in stable branches. So there
is no longer a need to test changes to master under the stable
branches. This change removes the stable jobs from pycadf.

Change-Id: I835bd002408e485f711d0a09afc6bb4e3395fbc4

commit_message:
Support scenarios for updating neutron quotas

* Add new scenario Quotas.neutron_update to exercise updating
  quotas for neutron
* Modify _update_quotas to be able to support clients which
  update quotas with an api different from nova and cinder
* Add test for ZaqarQueues list()

Co-Authored-By: Roman Vasilets <rvasilets@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Marco Morais <mmorais@yahoo-inc.com>

Change-Id: Ida19c02f831e1846bb96a239f4a2deb5ae417153

commit_message:
Raise bad request for missing 'label' in tenant network

While creating tenant network if 'label' is missing in
request body then, HTTPInternalServerError gets raised.

This patch handle above case and raise HTTPBadRequest for better
error handling.

Closes-Bug: #1419629

Change-Id: Ifd5c21257c10a93622fb2c94a0dc0986fefaf5d8

commit_message:
Fix get_floating_ip lookup for {"id": net_id"}

The `get_floating_ip' should accept its own return value.
Otherwise it tries to lookup for a floating_ip with id='{"id": net_id}'.

Change-Id: I7090b8e4b9a9b886d11aa6a4523de8d44346d901
Closes-Bug: #1419603

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-11-17 13:10:29.000000000', 'files': ['nova/db/sqlalchemy/api.py'], 'message': "Add _security_group_ensure_default() DBAPI method

According to the convention we use for DB API methods, every public
method should have a private counterpart. The difference between
those two is that the latter accepts an optional 'session' argument,
which makes it possible for the method to participate in the existing
database transaction.

security_group_ensure_default() was called inside instance_create()
and thus implicitly created a new concurrent db transaction, which
is now fixed by making a call to a private counterpart and passing

Closes-Bug: #1362233

Change-Id: Ifa1b6430328fde1ab0984f726bd8392bbd3f7ee5
(cherry picked from commit dbc46b99cc85402c087bb214c120bce2c65dfea9)
"}]
commit_message:
Add _security_group_ensure_default() DBAPI method

According to the convention we use for DB API methods, every public
method should have a private counterpart. The difference between
those two is that the latter accepts an optional 'session' argument,
which makes it possible for the method to participate in the existing
database transaction.

security_group_ensure_default() was called inside instance_create()
and thus implicitly created a new concurrent db transaction, which
is now fixed by making a call to a private counterpart and passing
the session instance.

Closes-Bug: #1362233

Change-Id: Ifa1b6430328fde1ab0984f726bd8392bbd3f7ee5
(cherry picked from commit dbc46b99cc85402c087bb214c120bce2c65dfea9)

commit_message:
Fix lack of device ownership enforcement for DVR routers

The enforcement rule was applied to centralized router interfaces, to avoid
a potential security vulnerabilty.

Even though DVR routers are fundamentally different from centralized routers,
there is no good reason as to why the rule should be skipped for DVR interfaces.

This patch sanitizes the insanity a bit and closes this potential loophole by
preventing the operation for DVR routers too.

Related-bug: #1243327
Closes-bug: #1410984

(cherry picked from commit 89025a8dd93918ac2967726ec7bb8ee5aa22d924)

Conflicts:
        neutron/db/db_base_plugin_v2.py

Change-Id: I048e6e3926e1c74cf9ecb63cfb53a0b1afb3c579

commit_message:
Fixes inconsistent import naming scheme

This patch is part of an effort to add a more consistent import naming scheme
to Horizon. Attempts to remove masking of the imports where it is unnecessary,
and make the masks consistent if they are needed. The verbosity/ consistency
should also aid with learning & review speed.

The rules followed are:
- Imports from Horizon are not renamed, so horizon views are just left
  as views, for example
- Imports are always prefixed with the relevant panel name
- Use "from .. import .. as ..." rather than just "import ... as ...".
  It is easier to see precisely what is bring imported in this case.
- Style where possible is:
  from ... \
      import ... as ...
- Removes masking from imports where it is unnecessary. There are many
  instances of masking "workflow_helpers", for example, masked as "helpers",
  "whelpers", "wf_helpers" or "work_helpers".

Examples (before -> after):
1)import openstack_dashboard.dashboards.project.data_processing. \
    utils.workflow_helpers as whelpers
  ->
  from openstack_dashboard.dashboards.project.data_processing.utils \
    import workflow_helpers

2)from openstack_dashboard.dashboards.project.data_processing. \
    jobs import tables as j_t
  ->
  from openstack_dashboard.dashboards.project.data_processing.jobs \
    import tables as jobs_tables

Change-Id: I5a625680927b622991552fe89566fd50999ceb98
Partial-Bug: 1411037

commit_message:
Implement Keystone domain creation

Keystone domain has to be created for Heat. This patch implements this
via helper script [1] since we don't have support for Keystone v3 API
in puppet-keystone yet. This implementation should be refactored as soon
as we will have v3 API available in puppet-keystone. For more info
please check [2].

[1] https://github.com/openstack/heat/blob/master/bin/heat-keystone-setup-domain
[2] https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1076172

Change-Id: I036a84eee6b9d0afa9a9ed96849494324ba4c4db
(cherry picked from commit 41608dc6c8e3248049c91c2a3c8647f0cbd7caad)

commit_message:
fix the value of query_spec.maxSample to advoid to be zero

code before:
VC_REAL_TIME_SAMPLING_INTERVAL = 20

samples_cnt = (int(duration / VC_REAL_TIME_SAMPLING_INTERVAL)
if duration else 1)
query_spec.maxSample = samples_cnt

if we set the value of "interval" in /etc/ceilometer/pipline.yaml to less
than 20,the value of "query_spec.maxSample" will be 0,which will cause
problem when use it to send request to vsphere server

Change-Id: Ibdb586109fe5334f3080539a40ff92badead837b
Closes-Bug:#1415307

Boot server w/ predefined internal network

Extend `_boot_server_with_network` to understand `internal_network`
argument that specifies an internal network to boot server with.

no good `network` context initializaton yet.

subject: VPNaaS: Remove duplication for exception - part 1
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-02-09 20:47:40.000000000', 'files': ['neutron_vpnaas/tests/unit/db/vpn/test_db_vpnaas.py', 'neutron_vpnaas/extensions/vpnaas.py', 'neutron_vpnaas/db/vpn/vpn_db.py'], 'message': "VPNaaS: Remove duplication for exception - part 1

As part of the Advanced Services split, the RouterInUseByVPNService
exception, which was moved to the neutron-vpnaas repo, was needed by
a Neutron test case, so it was temporarily left in the neutron repo,
and the definition in the neutron-vpnaas repo was temporarily assigned
to the Neutron definition. Reference commit df9dd769.

The refactoring of this code, will be done in three parts. In this
commit, check_router_in_use() will raise a Neutron RouterInUse exception
and the RouterInUseByVPNService definition will be removed.
Unit tests are added to test the two in-use methods, so that we have
coverage. Note: I don't see check_subnet_in_use() used, so it, and the
exception could be removed (as a separate commit)?

Part 2 will modify Neutron code to change the RouterInUse exception to
allow a reason string, and update the unit tests to check for a
RouterInUse exception, instead of RouterInUseByVPNService.

Part 3 will modify the VPN repo to include the service ID in the reason
field when raising a RouterInUse exception.

Change-Id: I5453e3be50c1c261d10c071c569ac7407c5b742d
Partially-Implements: blueprint services-split
"}]
commit_message:
VPNaaS: Remove duplication for exception - part 1

As part of the Advanced Services split, the RouterInUseByVPNService
exception, which was moved to the neutron-vpnaas repo, was needed by
a Neutron test case, so it was temporarily left in the neutron repo,
and the definition in the neutron-vpnaas repo was temporarily assigned
to the Neutron definition. Reference commit df9dd769.

The refactoring of this code, will be done in three parts. In this
commit, check_router_in_use() will raise a Neutron RouterInUse exception
and the RouterInUseByVPNService definition will be removed.
Unit tests are added to test the two in-use methods, so that we have
coverage. Note: I don't see check_subnet_in_use() used, so it, and the
exception could be removed (as a separate commit)?

Part 2 will modify Neutron code to change the RouterInUse exception to
allow a reason string, and update the unit tests to check for a
RouterInUse exception, instead of RouterInUseByVPNService.

Part 3 will modify the VPN repo to include the service ID in the reason
field when raising a RouterInUse exception.

Change-Id: I5453e3be50c1c261d10c071c569ac7407c5b742d
Partially-Implements: blueprint services-split

commit_message:
Add restart rados gateway task to post_deployment stage

Current task restarts rados gateway after deployment was completed.
It should run on all controllers, only if option - objects_ceph
is selected.

And restart should be performed prior to uploading of cirros image.
Glance communicates directly with rados gateway to access ceph.

related to blueprint granular-deployment-based-on-tasks

commit_message:
Switch to TLSv1 as SSLv3 is considered insecure and is disabled by default

Rabbitmq won't talk to us anymore if we try to use SSLv3 as it disabled
support for SSLv3. Openstack components use python's openssl
implementation which does not support TLSv1.1 and TLSv1.2 yet so we
just switch to TLSv1. Support for newer TLS should come with python
2.7.9+

Closes-Bug: #1409667
Change-Id: I3834decbc73a97a627023b132324a6c4aec2468a
(cherry picked from commit 7b801ad37ac36e5eddd3d844e3f483edcfa38442)

Makes kombu_ssl_* parameters optional when rabbit_use_ssl => true

The kombu_ssl_* parameters should not be required when rabbit_use_ssl => true
Rather, rabbit_use_ssl must be set to true if the kombu_ssl_* parameters are
used.

Change-Id: I1b2cbb15a7778c3d072409c43b39d1f41b7b48b6
Closes-Bug: 1356083
(cherry picked from commit 15b0a7dc825b1182f9e0e35c109ed7a6aaa51fd7)

commit_message:
Implement Keystone domain creation

Keystone domain has to be created for Heat. This patch implements this
via helper script [1] since we don't have support for Keystone v3 API
in puppet-keystone yet. This implementation should be refactored as soon
as we will have v3 API available in puppet-keystone. For more info
please check [2].

[1] https://github.com/openstack/heat/blob/master/bin/heat-keystone-setup-domain
[2] https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1076172

Change-Id: I036a84eee6b9d0afa9a9ed96849494324ba4c4db

commit_message:
Libvirt: Created Nova driver for Quobyte

Driver for Quobyte storage product.
Mounts respective Quobyte volume of VM images.
This is the Nova part of integrating Quobyte.
Corresponding Cinder Driver Blueprint:
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/cinder/+spec/quobyte-usp-driver
The Cinder driver has been merged into Cinder,
it's review can be found at:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/94186/

blueprint quobyte-nova-driver
DocImpact: Adding option 'quobyte_mount_point_base' and 'quobyte_client_cfg'

Change-Id: Ica1820031f1fc8b66d7ed7fe76ffeb985cf0ef35

commit_message:
Rework the sqlalchemy backend

We can just simplify the usage of an sqlalchemy if we just use
(we already have our own ORM like objects anyway) sqlalchemy core
in the first place and have a very tiny layer that converts back and
forth from our very limited object model that we use in our
persistence layer.

This change makes that adjustment, which makes it easier to read
and understand the actions the sqlalchemy backend is doing when
saving, reading and updating data, and avoids yet another layer
that isn't useful for our purposes anyway.

Change-Id: I911c509f65e7845aee86fed1622eaa56970741f2

commit_message:
New Cinder volume driver for openvstorage

Open vStorage is an open-source software defined storage VM storage
router, a layer in between Virtual machines and storage backends.
It is compatible with Swift (via S3) interface as backend and nova
compute nodes as frontend, it serves volumes via a virtual filesystem
 using .raw files. Multiple Storage Routers can coordinate between
them and allow live migration with near-zero copy (only local cache
is synced).
The driver implements basic volume operations (create, delete,
snapshot,clone volume, clone snapshot, create from image, upload to
 image).

Implements: blueprint open-vstorage-volume-driver
Change-Id: I4a195aacb34fb1300c158c2d8163887b913b6de8
